The Dow Jones Industrial Average is trading up Wednesday morning with shares of Pfizer and McDonald's seeing positive momentum for the index. The Dow DJIA, -1.67% is trading 72 points higher (0.3%), as shares of Pfizer PFE, -0.80% and McDonald's MCD, -1.52% have contributed to the index's intraday rally. Pfizer's shares are up $1.17, or 3.2%, while those of McDonald's are up $4.09, or 2.1%, combining for an approximately 36-point boost for the Dow. IBM IBM, +0.12%, Intel INTC, +0.27%, and Visa V, -2.13% are also contributing significantly to the gain. A $1 move in any one of the 30 components of the Dow equates to a 6.86-point swing.

